    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Equipment comprising pieces of openwork fabric made of twine, synthetic fibres, strong cord, or another material that forms meshes of a suitable size; they are placed in the water and used for catching fish. Fishing nets are among the oldest known human technologies.</Note_Text>
